race.comment: BLANC VISAGE (8) returned with real purpose at Gawler, swooping over the top and scoring with authority. She lacks early speed and may find herself in an awkward spot from the low draw, but her fresh win was too strong to ignore. DAISYDOO (6) is knocking on the door and looks ready to crack it after going down by a head last time. Cherry-ripe now, though will need a smart steer from the wide alley. MIC DROP (5) has come back in terrific order this prep, notching her third win last start when reeling them in with something up her sleeve. Freshened 35 days and kept ticking over with a Strathalbyn trial win. She's sure to be very competitive again. PURFECT LINE (10) improved to place last start and could progress further third up
